"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145273","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-09-26","<p>Additional funding announced by the Secretary of State in November 2016, for an additional 2,500 prison officer posts, was agreed with HM Treasury as part of the Autumn Statement 2016.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2019-09-26T14:56:47.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145273/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145273/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145273/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-09-06","Prison Officers: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 30 July 2019 to Question 280425, whether funding for the additional prison officers recruited is from (a) existing funding from his Department or (b) additional funding from the public purse.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","287921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145275","Department for International Development","false","2019-10-08","<p>Since the Yemen conflict started in 2015, our partners have reported two UK funded assets have been damaged by alleged airstrikes. These are a Norwegian Refugee Council warehouse in the Harradh area of Hajjah governorate on 21 June 2015 and a UNICEF water and sanitary health facility in Sahar district on 22 July 2018.</p><p> </p><p>We closely monitor such incidents, but we are not able to conduct investigations which would allow us to conclude which parties were responsible.</p><p> </p><p>Losses to DFID following the Norwegian Refugee Council warehouse incident were £3,127, while DFID suffered no direct losses as a result of damages to the UNICEF facility.</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-10-08T11:38:22.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145275/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145275/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145275/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-09-06","Yemen: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, pursuant to the Answer of 5 September 2019 to Question 282383 on Yemen: Overseas Aid, which UK funded assets were damaged and which parties were identified as responsible for that damage; and how much UK Aid funding has been spent on those facilities.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","287922"
