"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144991","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-09","<p>As announced by the Prime Minister on 25 August, all major UK airports have been instructed to introduce new 3D cabin baggage screening equipment by 1 December 2022.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2019-09-09T14:44:41.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144991/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144991/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144991/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-05","Airports: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has plans to introduce 3D baggage screening equipment at UK airports.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","287512"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144993","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-10-03","<p>Fisheries control and enforcement is a devolved matter. As such, it will continue to be for each Devolved Administration to decide how best to control its waters, and what new arrangements may be needed. The Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs (DEFRA) continues to work closely with the Devolved Administrations in Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland to ensure a coordinated approach to fisheries control and enforcement across UK waters.</p><p> </p><p>In England, the Marine Management Organisation on behalf of DEFRA has assessed the risk of increased illegal fishing when the UK leaves the EU, including under the scenario of doing so without a deal. As such DEFRA have decided to strengthen the allocated resources. This includes an increase to the number of Royal Navy vessels allocated to the task and increased sea time to enhance patrolling capacity at sea.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-10-03T14:27:28.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144993/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144993/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144993/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-05","Navy: Fisheries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans he has to increase the capacity of the UK’s marine patrol vessels to patrol fishing waters in the event that the UK leaves the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","287578"
