"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145006","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-09-09","<p>We are confident that there are no significant safety or environmental concerns (radiological or conventional) with the current storage processes. All laid-up submarines at the Rosyth and Devonport Dockyards undergo regular inspection and maintenance to comply with the very highest safety and environmental standards. This includes continual monitoring, annual surveys and periodic docking for re-preservation of the hulls. All aspects of afloat storage, including potential environmental impacts and radiological safety, are regulated by the Defence Nuclear Safety Regulator.</p>","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan",,"2019-09-09T16:13:28.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145006/answer","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145006/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145006/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-05","Submarines: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the long-term environmental effect of delaying the dismantling of decommissioned submarines in UK dockyards.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","287591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145007","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-09-09","<p>An investigation has been conducted into the flooding incident that took place in HMS Queen Elizabeth. The incident did not involve a temporary pipe coupling and there are no such couplings in HMS Queen Elizabeth or HMS Prince of Wales.</p>","Berwick-upon-Tweed","Anne-Marie Trevelyan","287572 ; 287593","2019-09-09T16:15:05.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145007/answer","Biography information for Anne-Marie Trevelyan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145007/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145007/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-05","HMS Prince of Wales and HMS Queen Elizabeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons temporary couplings were used on HMS Queen Elizabeth and HMS Prince of Wales instead of permanent fixtures.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","287592"
