"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145159","Treasury","false","2019-09-27","<p>It is not possible to produce meaningful estimates of the paybills of employers in specific geographical areas. HMRC has information on where Pay As You Earn (PAYE) schemes are registered, though not on the workplaces of the employer. Many large employers will have various workplaces across the UK and will operate multiple PAYE schemes, or outsource their payroll to a payroll provider based in a different location.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-09-27T13:58:55.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145159/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145159/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145159/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-09-05","Companies: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the total payroll is of companies in England that have a payroll (a) over and (b) under £3 million.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","287470"
