"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145173","Northern Ireland Office","true","2019-09-09","<p><del class="ministerial">It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</del></p><p><ins class="ministerial">My discussions with the political parties have been focused to date on the urgent need to restore devolved government in Northern Ireland. Officials in my Department are exploring options for marking the centenary of Northern Ireland in 2021.</ins></p>","Skipton and Ripon","Julian Smith",,"2019-09-09T16:51:43.23Z","2019-10-02T16:30:14.683Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145173/answer","Biography information for Julian Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145173/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145173/answer","Skipton and Ripon","Julian Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1145173/answer/previousversion/135657","Biography information for Julian Smith","21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-09-05","Anniversaries: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions he has had with political parties on plans to mark the centenary of Northern Ireland in 2021.","false","Biography information for Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","Lagan Valley","Sir Jeffrey M. Donaldson","287501"
