"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144592","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-09-09","<p>Since the formation of NHS England’s Cross-System Sepsis Programme Board in 2015, good progress has been made in recognising sepsis early. The Programme Board brings together a group of front-line experts from across the health and care system to take action to improve the identification, diagnosis and management of sepsis in children, young people and adults across the National Health Service.</p><p>In September 2018, the Government launched a suspicion of sepsis dashboard. This allows hospitals to identify how many patients are admitted with a severe bacterial infection, are at risk of sepsis, to track their improvements, and supports clinicians in identifying patients who should be screened for sepsis.</p>","Mid Bedfordshire","Ms Nadine Dorries",,"2019-09-09T17:18:33.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144592/answer","Biography information for Ms Nadine Dorries","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144592/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144592/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-04","Sepsis: Diagnosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps he is taking to improve early diagnosis of sepsis.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","286743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144593","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Department funds health research through the National Institute for Health Research (NIHR). The NIHR welcomes funding applications for research into any aspect of human health. However, the NIHR has not conducted any research into links between head injuries sustained through sport and motor neurone disease.</p><p>It is not usual practice to ring-fence funds for particular topics or conditions. Applications are subject to peer review and judged in open competition, with awards being made on the basis of the importance of the topic to patients and health and care services, value for money and scientific quality. In all disease areas, the amount of NIHR funding depends on the volume and quality of scientific activity.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2019-09-09T17:30:07.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144593/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144593/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144593/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-04","Motor Neurone Disease: Sports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether he has commissioned research into the connection between head injuries sustained through sport and and motor neurone disease.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","286744"
