"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144637","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Government is committed to meeting the additional health needs of thalidomide survivors and to giving them the same opportunities that others enjoy. The current health grant is a central element of this. We will be drawing on evidence in due course from the Thalidomide Trust regarding the value and benefits of the grant when considering arrangements for when the current 10 year grant ends in 2023. Future funding decisions will be undertaken as part of the appropriate Spending Review process in due course.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2019-09-09T17:18:05.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144637/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144637/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144637/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-04","Thalidomide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will make it his policy to renew the health grant for thalidomide survivors in April 2023.","false","Biography information for Tonia Antoniazzi","Gower","Tonia Antoniazzi","286835"
